Approximately 20 to 30 percent of patients require intensive care and mechanical ventilation.
In addition to the lower respiratory tract, the stomach and intestines, liver and kidneys can also become infected with this serious disease, most likely a cytokine storm, which can be especially deadly for patients with weakened immune systems.
